inn1.comm: back of a length, just outside off, left alone and good carry through to the keeper
short of a length, angled into the body, nudged into the leg side where Billings is quickly in from square leg
touch fuller outside off, 85mph, left alone
first aggressive stroke, and Guptill gets beaten as he drives, drawn into a fuller delivery...more encouraging carry
well bowled, close to the stumps! Nips back from a short length, takes an inside edge into Guptill's back leg and lobs over the top of the bails
extra bounce, that's hurt Guptill. Jumps from back of a length and takes him on the gloves. Has a grimace. Very good over
full outside off, driven to mid-off
dragged down and that's pulled powerfully in front of square, whistles to deep midwicket
good response from Jordan, gets it outside off and there's a touch of bounce to beat the top edge
beaten again! McCullum trying another flashing stroke square of the wicket
sound the bugle! McCullum comes down the pitch, takes a step to the leg side, and has a wild mow at a length ball...not in the same postcode
and there's a proper defensive shot, back of a length on off stump, defended to the bowler
full at off stump, he comes forward and drives to the left of mid-off
makes a connection this time, a full delivery and he heaves it over wide mid-on...stayed still in the crease this time, there was no change. Didn't time it very well
swings a full delivery down to long leg
tight on middle and off, 86mph, defended back to the bowler
well bowled, short of a length outside off and holds its line, Guptill felt for it before withdrawing his bat
dragged down short and wide, he latches on with a square cut in front of point...was in the air, but well wide of the fielder
down the pitch and another huge swing at a back-of-a-length delivery
back of a length at off stump, 87mph, defended into the off side
short delivery, he rolls his wrists nicely on the pull, played with his front foot off the ground, and finds long leg
defended into the off side, placed between cover and mid-off
slips this down the leg side, first wide of the day
stand and deliver, throws his hands through a full delivery outside off and sends it screaming square through the off side
much straighter, cramping McCullum for room, defended into the covers
and now Guptill on the drive, any width is being dispatched, this one is driven on the up wide of mid-off...shows the trueness of the pitch
tightens the line, onto off stump, defended and the ball squirts out to square leg
back of a length outside off, 83mph, punched square into the covers
excellent delivery, in the channel outside off, just nibbling away off the seam and it beats the outside edge
not convincing, but it's the first six of the day...a short delivery, Guptill pulls and it gets a meaty top edge which just has the legs to clear the deep square boundary
back outside off, resists having a dart, left alone
gets a good amount of bat on this one, uses his feet again to Jordan then takes a length delivery over the on side...not quite the connection for six, one bounce
over the off side this time, and this one clears the rope at wide third man...down the pitch again, Jordan drags the length back, and McCullum scythes it over backward point
that's huge! Out of the ground. No doubt that came out of the middle. Short, again, from Jordan and this time McCullum pulls mightily over deep square leg. New ball, please

chance! Stokes wasn't expecting that at second slip...McCullum on the charge, goes for the pull and gets a top onto his shoulder and helmet which then flies over a startled Stokes to third man. Given runs
full outside leg stump, shovelled down to long leg...fifty on the board, and the first over was a maiden
back of a length at off stump, defended to backward point
pushes firmly at a delivery outside off, opens the face and finds third man
full on middle and off, takes a leading edge as Guptill defends but all along the ground
short and wide, called a wide but could easily have been four (or six)
pushed down the leg side, Steve Davis stretches out his arms again
short of a length outside off, flies in the air as Guptill drives off the back foot but goes fine of backward point
the speed of McCullum's wrists into play, slices a short delivery high over backward point and wide of third man
good comeback, goes fuller and straight, McCullum jabs down and gets an inside edge to the leg side
a neat punch off the back foot to the left of mid-off so he keeps the strike
back of a length on middle, pushed firmly towards mid-on

the change has worked! Excellent catch by Stokes. McCullum went for another pull, the ball seemed to skid onto McCullum, he was rushed into the shot and it went high towards midwicket. Still, Stokes had to make decent ground as the ball came over his shoulder. Well judged.
back of a length on off stump, 89mph, defended into the covers
touch fuller, Guptill presses forward and drives, gets a thick outside edge down to third man
short outside off, 87mph, Williamson sways out of the line
on off stump, defended with the soft hands which are such a feature of Williamson's batting, runs towards that fine gully
gets a thick inside part of the bat and it runs wide of mid-on
gets across onto off stumps and flicks a straight delivery into midwicket
full outside off, he walks into a defensive push which finds mid-off
dragged down short, Guptill hasn't quite got his timing, he pulls it in front of square through midwicket but it came from low down the bat
fuller on off stump, blocked into the leg side with a slightly closed face
back of a length outside off, 84mph, defended to the covers
pushes forward into a length delivery and places to the covers
sharp running, drop into the leg side and good understanding to rotate the strike
that's a fantastic shot, no issues about timing on this occasion, he punches a back-of-a-length delivery between cover and mid-off
tightens the line, on middle and off, 86mph, defended towards mid-off
superb, again...that's his best of the day so far as he punches a full, straight delivery down the on-side of the stumps
defended towards the leg side
back of a length outside off, 81mph, driven to the covers from the back foot
fuller on middle and off, defended to the man at short mid-on
slips down the leg side, called a wide
full outside off, 83mph, left alone
width outside off, but Williamson's drive finds point
comes forward into a firm-handed push, the ball rolls into the leg side
works a short-of-a-length delivery neatly through midwicket with a back-foot whip
pushed down the leg side
nice piece of timing, works a straight delivery off his body through midwicket and it rolls quickly over the wide square on this ground
short of a length outside off, dropped into the leg side and more good running...as important as the boundaries
full outside off, dabbed down in front of gully...good pace at 87mph
gets over the top of a short ball, keeps the balls along the ground as he pulls to long leg
full on off stump, 85mph, defended to the covers
back of a length, 90mph, good wheels, punched towards mid-on
lovely stroke, classy from Williamson, he gets onto his toes and punches with a straight bat through the covers
across onto off stump, defended back to the bowler
another well-judged single, pushed towards mid-on where Finn is a little on his heels
on the back foot again, punches to the cover ring which has now been reinforced
angled into the batsman, flicked to midwicket with the bottom hands
full outside off, 83mph, defended to backward point
dropped in short, Guptill plays a well-controlled punchy pull to deep square
back of a length and whipped to midwicket
on off stump, defended to cover
back of a length outside off, punched sweetly just to the left of mid-off and it turns into quite a sharp single
fuller on off stump, closes the face and works it through midwicket and placed with the right amount of force to allow him back for a second
defended solidly up to mid-off
works a straight delivery to deep square and there's a horrid misfield at deep square by Hales, who went one-handed, then didn't try to chase after the ball
full on off stump, cut to backward point
nicely bowled, flighted full, brings Williamson onto the front foot as he defends
a full toss which is whipped towards mid-on
full outside off, he gets a good stride forward and drives to long-off
a touch short outside off and it's cut to deep point
opens with a wide down leg
foot outside off, back of a length, Williamson punches this to extra-cover
tighter line and this is tucked back up the wicket, Williamson slightly cramped
touch fuller, pressed from the crease out on the off side now
almost the same delivery and stroke, fielded at cover
another back foot press out into the covers, pretty tight stuff from Stokes
drags this down and Williamson pulls but deep square is able to go to his right and make the save
floated up on middle and off, driven back to the bowler
more air and Guptill meets this on the full and whacks it wide of mid-on
back on a full length just outside off, this is driven to extra-cover
tighter line and Guptill driving gets a thick outside edge to point, nicely bowled that, some drift in and gripped away
loses his length again and once more Guptill is able to lean forward and smack a low full toss inside long-off
firm push down to long-off now for a just a single
length ball around off, this pushed out into the covers
fuller length, this is driven to mid-off
straight, Guptill drops this into midwicket and sprints hard to come back for the second to bring up a half-century in 51 balls
back just outside off, this is driven towards mid-off, too close to the fielder for a single
straighter and this deflects off the thigh pad towards midwicket

back of a length just outside off, Guptill pulls and picks out short midwicket! Trap set there by Eoin Morgan and Guptill has been taken as planned. Going for a paddle pull, not really a full-bloodied stroke, but it was still struck firmly and it was a very smart catch from Chris Jordan going to his left, a good height for him and he held on well
a skip down the track to drive this to long-off
straight delivery, Taylor playing round the pad a little gets this up to short midwicket
a little more air, this is flicked to mid-on
more of a length ball, Taylor forward to block in front of middle and off
similar line, blocked back up the wicket this time
this pitches outside leg and turns to take the outside edge with Taylor looking to turn it around the corner, ends up running past slip
full length a foot wide of off stump, Williamson shoulders arms
fuller and straighter, this is dug out back to the bowler
short and wide, poor ball, Williamson cuts it to the point fence, pressure release
very full and wide of off stump, this is dug out to backward point who claims a catch but surely it was a bump ball and the umpire's aren't going to bother to even check, right decision too
wide line again and this is driven out past extra-cover, nice timing
another drive, this more classical and timed past mid-off, couple of times there Stokes losing his line
length ball on the stumps, this is blocked back to the bowler
full toss but gets away with this, slapped out only to deep midwicket
back of a length, some turn, Williamson dabs it up into midwicket
full length, this is blocked playing forward
delicate sweep from off stump out to deep square, controlled stroke
tossed up around off stump, this is driven down to long-off
full drifting into the pads, this is helped on it's way to fine leg
this comes back a little to beat the inside edge, takes two pads down to third man
full length ball around off, blocked coming forward
length just outside off, Williamson stays leg side of it and plays a delicate late cut inside gully
not as much width but Williamson still manages to dab this down to third man
short and wide and cut and dropped at backward point, chance for Jason Roy diving to his right with two hands, a tough one because it went quickly but he did get two hands there
full length around middle and off, Williamson plays forward to block
down the track chipping leg side in the air but just out of the reach of a diving mid-on going to his right, Roy again, he got a fingertip to it that maybe saved a run
full length around middle and leg, this is pressed back up to the bowler
drags this down and Williamson pulls nicely to split the leg side deep fielders
tad short of a length outside off, Williamson rocking back to cut out to deep cover
paddle sweep of a length through square leg
length ball at the body, this is dropped down through square leg for a quick single
short enough to pull and Williamson again picks the gap square on the leg side
outside off now, Williamson waits and drops it wide of gully for a single to bring up fifty in 52 balls, usual nice controlled knock
straighter, this takes the thigh pad for a single through square leg
similar ball, this time tucked out into the deep
short ball that climbs on Taylor and he wears it on the side of the head before the ball deflects down to third man
driven from just outside off, only just short of short extra-cover
full length down the leg side, this is paddle swept to deep square
tad short just outside off, this is cut to deep cover
not for the first time Rashid gets on to turn across Taylor playing to leg, this takes an outside edge past slip
slider, touch short, Taylor pats it back up the wicket
tossed up, Taylor dances down to it, meets it on the full, and slaps this to wide long-on for a one-bounce four
around the wicket, full length on leg stump, this is tucked out through midwicket
slides across Taylor who sits back to late cut but only finds short third man
straighter line, this is flicked back to the bowler
fuller, this is flicked out down to long-on
down the track to make this a low full toss, plays a firm punch down to long-on
played at firmly, takes a leading edge towards mid-off, he wasn't aiming there but still gets a single
premeditated paddle sweep from just outside off backward of square on the leg side, gets a couple
same again, this to a straighter ball, gets a bit of a top edge but it flies over the keeper for two more
low full toss, this is swept hard out to deep square
tad short, pulled out to the same fielder, Hales going to his left-hand side
tad short again, this is cut out to deep cover
quicker ball, pushed off the back foot to long-on
down the track to make this a full toss and places this really well between deep midwicket and long-on, timed very well too
hangs back to late cut, finds backward point
shuffle down the wicket, works this down to long-on
full length just outside off, this is flicked to long-on again
step down to drive, extra-cover saves well with a diving right hand, parries to mid-off
straight line, this is worked through midwicket but only one available with Hales in quickly off the rope
short enough to encourage Williamson to rock back and he pulls into the boundary rope at wide long-on, picked up well
off stump line, this is driven to mid-off
floated up on a similar line and this time Williamson lifts this over mid-off, just a gentle lift but it timed so well to get into the rope, great shot
almost the same stroke, went a little higher and got four more, again the timing and placement was excellent
back foot this time, punching to long-off who has now gone back
back forcing this to long-on this time, 200 up
full length wide of off stump, this is driven out through point and they get two as deep cover goes to his left
quicker ball and Taylor waits for it to come to him just outside off and late cuts nicely inside short third man
over the wicket, this is flicked from just outside off to long-on
straight line, Williamson flicks off the back foot between the leg side deep fielders and they sprint for two more, top batting
fires this down the leg side, well taken by Buttler
down the track and yorks himself, digs it out back to the bowler
stays in the crease here and presses down to long-on
short of a length outside off, defended to backward point
similar length and this time Williamson isn't defending, latches on with a strong pull in front of square
fantastic batting, Finn pushes his length fuller and Williamson responds with a lofted straight drive
ooh, nearly chops this into his stumps, Finn goes back to a short delivery and it's defended down off the inside edge just wide of leg stump
and again! Short of a length, defended with soft hands and it bounces back very near to leg stump...Williamson playing chicken with it
short, rolls his wrists as he pulls to long leg
tucked off the body to deep square
plays and misses as he pulls at a length delivery
full outside off stump, 88mph, driven firmly into the ground to cover
slower ball which slides down the leg side so he'll need to bowl that again
chopped down to third man from outside off
flicks a length delivery to midwicket
a bouncer, over middle and off, Williamson ducks
good delivery at off stump, squares up Taylor a touch and takes a thick outside edge towards backward point who manages to cut off the single
nearly another mix-up between these two! Short of a length, dropped towards backward point, it was Williamson's call but Taylor wanted none of it. Williamson manages to turn around and get back
finds backward point again, trying to angle a short delivery to third man...
touch fuller, rolls his fingers across the seam, dropped into the off side and this time the understanding is good for the quick single
nips back off the seam and takes him high on the pad, another cutter from Finn
another slower ball, low full toss outside off, but it's too costly as Williamson clothes it to deep midwicket
comes down the pitch outside leg stump, then angles down to third man
a bouncer, Taylor hooks and gets a top edge straight back over his head and the keeper
full at off stump, 87mph, dug out towards mid-on
width outside off, cut firmly to backward point
a straighter, shorter delivery which is pulled to deep square
a bouncer which is angling down the leg side but Stokes gets away with it
worked from outside off to midwicket
full at middle, pushed back to the bowler
flicked from outside off along the ground towards midwicket who, slightly unluckily, palms it away for a single as he dives
good stuff from Rashid, tight at middle and off, pushed back to him
oops, that comes out as big full toss, Williamson uses his feet but doesn't take full advantage as he finds long-on
goes back to a slightly shorter delivery, a legspinner that turns, and cuts to deep cover
dropped, that was drilled at short cover, full outside off and Taylor lay into it, Root couldn't hang on to his left
worked off the pads to deep square leg
gives himself room outside off and then is unable to reach a delivery outside off

caught at mid-on off a full toss, which is called no-ball on field! Williamson taken by surprise, the ball dips on him, skews it without any timing and it's well caught by Plunkett diving forward...it goes up to the third umpire, who rules it's below waist height so it's given out
a bouncer over off stump, sails over Elliott's head...close to a wide
well bowled! That zipped off the surface, short of a length and beats Elliott for pace at 88pm...Buttler thinks there was a sound, but no one else that interested
full outside off, driven to deep cover...oh dear, he's overstepped
slung wide outside off and driven firmly down to long-off
that's clean! And it's the slog sweep! Picked up from outside off and deposited into the stands at deep midwicket. Lovely way to go to fifty

run out chance! Elliott was gone. Dropped into the off side (nice ball, incidentally, which spun) and Elliott was racing up the pitch but again Taylor hadn't move. The throw to the non-striker's end by Billings misses
pushed into the off side
full and driven through cover
floated up outside off, Elliott uses his feet and drives in the air for a little while down to long-off
full toss outside off and he threads it through the off side, bit of a freebie
beaten again, good pace from Stokes at 87mph, and slides past the edge as Elliott tries to open the face
lovely piece of timing and placement, just eases into a length delivery and places it through the gap between point and cover
guides down to third man, wide of the slip
cut for six! Short outside off, Taylor throws everything behind it and sends it high over backward point
flicked away from off stump to midwicket
down the pitch and carves a length delivery over cover without much timing but they still collect three
dragged down short and Taylor moving through the gears now as he pulls strongly wide of the man who is more deep midwicket than deep square
full and straight, flicked off his pads and it races to short boundary at fine leg
full outside off, quite wide but just inside the guideline so Taylor's leave means it's a dot ball
mighty blow! That's into the second tier of the OCS stand...picks up a full delivery outside off and heaves it over deep midwicket with a hefty dose of bottom hand
comes forward into a full ball outside off and drives to mid-off
short of a length outside and that's a lovely deft touch as he deflects it fine of third man
short outside off, and called wide
short of a length, dropped into off side, has to dive to get back into his ground
full at the stumps and flicked to midwicket
superb placement from Taylor, he jumps in the air to attack this short ball and upper cuts it wide of third man...both feet off the ground as he made contact
back full at off stump, blocked to the bowler
that's a massive full toss! No doubt about the no-ball this time and Taylor does well to ramp it to third man
full and jabbed into the pitch, bounces over Finn to long-off
full delivery just outside off, this is driven up to mid-off and they scamper a quick single
length just outside off, this is dabbed to backward point and they sprint a single that Taylor has to be quick for making his ground at the non-striker's end
only just back of a length and pulled over square leg, picked it up really well, timed into the stands
slower ball outside off, Elliott is onto this very quickly and heaves it over long-on, 300 up
steps to leg and opens up the off side for a glorious drive past mid-off, timed well enough to get this out to the rope

full and straight, Elliott shuffling across his stumps trying to flick leg side, misses and is given out lbw! Looked straight enough, umpire Davis raising the finger, Elliott declines the review after consulting with his partner but that looked good live. Yorker length, angled in, caught Elliott on the boot and surely that was going on to hit leg stump at least
full at the pads, this is tucked out through square leg and they get a single
from nowhere, nibbles this away from the outside edge and beats the bat, length ball held it's line
straighter line, this is tucked up through midwicket
fuller ball and this is worked out wide of deep square and they run hard for two more
foot outside off, opens the face on this to steer a single down to third man
back on around middle and off, this is pushed back up to the bowler
full length just outside off, enough width for Ronchi to swing his hands through the line and strikes is superbly over long-off, gorgeous timing
bumper now, on line, Ronchi ducks
straighter line, this is flicked leg side and gets it over the head of long leg, only just carries the fielder but over his head it went, shortest boundary down there
low full toss, dabbed down from off stump, it bounces up to backward point
another low full toss, this time bunted down to long-off
same length but too wide outside off now
foot outside off and driven out to deep cover-point
low full toss around off, this is turned out to long-on for a quick single
short ball that follows Ronchi backing away to leg, tries to uppercut and misses
makes room for himself again and this time whacks a length ball over long-off, superb timing, clearing the front leg and swinging to good effect
similar line, Ronchi gets inside the line of this and steers it past short long leg
full length slides down the leg side via some pad to Buttler
slower ball on a length around off stump, Ronchi getting outside leg again and smashes this over cover, timing is so good once again
very full a foot or so outside off, this is driven at and misses
low full toss around middle and off, this is whacked over midwicket, missed the length and paid the penalty
makes this pitch and Taylor tries to swing it leg side and misses completely
wide line outside off, too wide
back on off stump, this is rolled out to deep cover
full toss just outside off, Ronchi can only drive it on the bounce to long-off
very full just outside off, this is calmly stroked out to deep cover-point
length at the pads, this is dabbed out through square leg for a quick single

steps to leg, tries to slap a back of a length ball over the off side and gets a thin edge behind! Useful wicket for England because Ronchi was looking very dangerous but here has just miscued a cut stroke and got a feather edge through to Buttler. Some relief for England
full delivery sliding across the leftie who drives out to deep cover
straight line tucked into square leg, Santner wants a single but is sent back and had substitute David Willey hit the non-striker's end stumps direct, Santner was gone
bit of width outside off and Taylor chops this wide of third man, steered away very nicely
back onto off stump and this is pressed back to Finn's left hand
back of a length, Santner clears his front leg and swats this over mid-on, bit of a slap but effective
clearing the front leg again, aiming off side this time misses
slower ball on the leg stump, this is clipped out to deep midwicket
length ball at the off stump, Taylor swings right across the line and gets it backward of square but Finn makes a smart save with an outstretched right hand
low full toss on the stumps, this is driven into the covers
slower ball outside off, Taylor slashes at this and gets a thick top edge down to third man
full on the stumps, this is flicked out to deep midwicket
hard square drive to a full ball, half-saved by a diving point, the deep man cleans up
low full toss around off stump, this is dug out down towards long-on and they charge back for the second as the ball rolls slowly down the ground

short ball just outside off, pulled out to deep midwicket and that is Ross Taylor's century! A fine innings from 87 balls has played really well today, not looked in great touch all tour really but he has ground out runs and here has looked pretty fluid
back of a length, Santner looks to pull and misses
steps inside this back of a length ball and heaves it leg side wide of long-on, nicely timed, races one bounce over the rope
full length just outside off, right in the slot for Taylor to swing it over long-on, he absolutely nails it way back into the stand
gets the yorker in, Taylor manages it to steers this down to long leg
Santner looks for the leg side rope and gets an inside edge via the pad into midwicket, Stokes himself fields
low full toss on off stump, slapped straight to mid-off where Morgan fumbles and they can get back for a second, no excuse there really
fuller length, same line, same stroke and this time Morgan fields successfully
manages to steer this through the off side, timed well and placed past the cover fielder
full toss outside off, this is mistimed up to mid-on, they run regardless
low full toss and this is carefully steered out through square leg, finds the gap perfectly again and this skips away wide of deep midwicket
slips this down leg, Taylor misses with a flick
full length on the stumps, this is dug out leg side and they sprint a couple before long-on can get in

very full on the stumps again, Taylor misses flicking to leg, not out given but England try the review. No bat involved, is this slipping down leg? Well not really, Hawk Eye has it taking a huge chunk of leg stump but only umpire's call so it stays on the field
another excellent yorker, flicks the pad and runs into the covers
length ball just outside off, Santner swings hard and gets a thick outside edge that flies down to third man on the bounce, just a single

inn2.comm: length ball down the leg side and Jason Roy has done better than Tuesday!
two feet outside off, Roy shoulders arms
back of a length at the body, this is tucked down into square leg
steers this past square leg now and Roy is away with a couple
middle and off line now, Roy forward playing into midwicket
tad short and Roy can pull this and gets it through square leg again, this races across the square for four
step down the track but just blocks a length ball to cover
but he starts on leg stump and gets clipped away fine
that's a terrific stroke, drives a back-of-a-length delivery at the top of the bounce in front of square
touch fuller, this time he's into the front foot and places it through the off side
good delivery, full and a hint of swing into Hales, jabbed out into the covers
full at off stump, driven straight of mid-off but he's able to get across
back of a length, on middle and leg, defended towards midwicket
leading edge, but it loops over cover...trying to work a short-of-a-length delivery into the leg side and the ball just held up off the pitch
fuller on off stump, defended back to the bowler
full outside off, reaching well away from his body to try to drive and gets a thick top edge which flies wide of second slip
now he's down the pitch and having a heave to the leg side, misses and isn't far from being bowled
full on off stump, brings him forward and he defends to cover
dropped, good delivery outside off, moves away to take the outside edge and travels at a good height to Nathan McCullum at second slip who can't take it despite two grabs
width outside off, cut to backward point
full on middle and off, driven firmly to mid-off
short on leg stump, goes for a pull and the ball loops off his arm
that's basically a swipe across the line at a good-length delivery, gets taken on the back leg
very full outside off, he jabs over the top it without making contact
tries to pull again, it was short of a length, but he gets beaten under the bottom edge...Boult responds with a maiden
full on middle and off, defended on the walk to mid-on
comes forward, drives on the up and finds mid-off
too straight, angled into pads and he flicks it away wide of short fine-leg
full outside off, swinging away, 84mph, left alone
comes down the pitch at a short-of-a-length delivery and tries to pull but doesn't make contact
a positive stride onto the front foot, pushed just to the left of mid-off
short delivery, Roy pulls and it is spliced high in the air but falls into the wide open spaces on the leg side
a bit of mindless swinging going on right now, Hales tries to fetch a length delivery from outside off and take it over the leg side
tighter line, angling into Hales from round the wicket, defended firmly to mid-on...some swing on offer for Boult
a bouncer angled over middle and leg, Hales lets it go over his back
back over the wicket, another short ball at a slippery 87mph and it beats Hales' top edge as he goes for the pull
full at the stumps, dug out to mid-on
makes room outside leg, Southee follows him with a full delivery which Roy then drills perfectly straight into the non-striker's stumps
back of a length, defended into the off side without looking entirely comfortable
short and at the body, Roy pulls sweetly but picks out deep square leg
low full toss outside off, hint of swing, pushed into the covers
back of a length, nips into Hales, defended to the leg side
flicked off the pads to deep square
hello there! That's another massive six to add to today's tally, a full delivery around off stump and Hales launches it high over long-on into the crowd
and now he drives serenely through the off side, a very classical shot this time as Boult over-pitches a touch from round the wicket
pulls and misses at a shorter delivery
nicely bowled, over the wicket, full at the stumps and takes a thick outside edge wide of backward point
full outside off, beats Roy on the inside edge as he comes forward to drive, lost his shape on the shot as it swung back...bat at a very odd angle
and again! Beat two in two, another one that just offers to swing back from outside off - such a good skill for a left-armer - and Roy is driving at fresh air
full at off stump, driven hard into the pitch and it bounces over Southee in his follow through
a straight full toss, Roy moves to the leg side to give himself room and drives it powerfully through the off side...not a million miles from a diving covr
now he pulls a short ball in front of square, not quite out of the middle and deep square keeps them to a single
short of middle and off, he ducks
full at off stump, driven firmly back at Southee who parries it away
low full toss which he works towards midwicket and doesn't find a gap
over the wicket, full outside off, driven to cover
that's meaty, but not quite six...Hales picks up a length delivery and drives it over mid-on, just short of the boundary rope
this one does have the legs! A delightful pick-up flick over the leg side, not just brute strength, excellent timing, as he deposits it over deep midwicket
shorter of length, Hales' eyes light up at a pull shot but he misses out
a very short delivery outside off, climbs over the top of Hales' bat as he tries to fetch it into the leg side
he's creamed that! That made a proper crunch off the bat, another short ball and it came out of the screws for Hales as he laruped his pull in front of square
tucked into the leg side
slightly shorter, he's onto the back foot and eases it down to long-on
brings out the reverse sweep and connects very cleanly, sending this just behind point on the off side

this is tight! A strong throw from Santner at deep midwicket, skims it into the keeper...has Roy made it with a full-length dive? Looks like he might have. Made us of every inch. He had work the ball through the leg side and decided to take on Santner's arm
pushed down the ground
played in the off side

for a second this looked huge from Roy as he launched a drive over long-on, but it wasn't quite out of the pitch and pitched in the outfield like a chip down the fairway...Santner does really well to flick it back
angled across, left alone outside off
another short one which is pulled powerfully but straight at deep square-leg this time
full outside off, Hales walks across his crease and then finds backward point
a sharp bouncer at 87mph which beats Hales as he goes for the pull...lively contest this one
well, that was strange...somehow he has got a boundary. It was a slower bouncer from McClenaghan, Hales ends up trying to leave the delivery and the ball takes the back of the bat down to fine leg
uses his feet but the ball then takes inside edge into the pads
short outside off, he rocks forward then back and drives strong well in front of the cover sweeper
picks him out! The reverse sweep brings his downfall, didn't keep the ball down and Taylor did not have to move an inch at short third man
eased down the ground to get off the mark
he dives across in his follow through to cut of Hales' push to the on side
this time he forces one past short midwicket to long-on
a strong straight drive, in the air but well short of long-off
angled into middle and leg, hint of turn, defended to the on side
a slog-sweep out to deep midwicket
this one grips outside off and turns quite sharply to defeat Hales' attempt to slog sweep
a bit of touch from Hales, guides it fine of short third man and that brings up his maiden ODI fifty from 43 balls
short outside off, cut to the cover sweeper
goes back to a shorter delivery, hurries onto him a touch and he can only play it back to the bowler
paddles another short ball behind square
full at the stumps, Root works into midwicket
touch quicker and flatter, uses his feet and flicks it wide of midwicket
punched down the ground to long-on
dragged down short, Root on one knee as he pulls through square leg...no hanging round when McCullum is bowling
nicely driven through the off side, placed wide of the sweeper and they scamper between the wickets...hundred up in good time
extra bounce this time, beats Root's top edge as he tries to cut...spun, too
full at the stumps, pushed into the covers

he's got him! That's a huge wicket for Santner. Root getting too far under this slog-sweep, getting more height than distance, he had to reach for it a little. Nathan McCullum takes a well-judged catch at midwicket
oh lovely delivery, angled in, spins away to beat the outside edge

tries a slog sweep from outside off and Hales picks out deep midwicket! Straight to the fielder a few yards inside the rope and an easy catch for Trent Boult. England losing wickets quickly here to kill their early momentum. Hales was well set but just didn't get enough of this, it was a bit of a top edge and never threatened to clear the boundary. A few strokes finding the fielders and England are suddenly in trouble
reverse-sweep first ball, Paul Nixon-style, can't quite evade deep cover who does well going to his right
full on middle and leg, this is tucked out to deep midwicket
forward just defending in front of off stump
full ball down leg, swung at and missed
leg side line again, this flicks the pad and runs inside short long leg for a leg bye
fired in back of a length, Stokes back on his stumps chopping it off a thick outside edge down towards third man
bit of air here, Stokes just dabbing this into the covers
angled in to the pads, this is a delicate deflection past the 45 and a long chase out to the boundary, does well
flighted just outside off, grips a little and takes a thick inside edge to midwicket
some more turn, this bounces up off the pad to the keeper
backs to leg and taps out through point, they run hard but can't get back for the second
slips this down leg
off stump line, Morgan slog sweeps with the turn and gets all of it over wide long-on, well struck
steps across the stumps to push a single fine of the 45
steps to leg and looks to smash over the off side, gets a wild top edge that loops safe over slip and backward of point
another big swing, another big edge, this loops over extra-cover, very luck
slog swept into the scoreboard, nailed it from middle stump way back over midwicket
just outside off, cut hard out to the off side sweeper
forward to press gently down the ground to long-on
back foot drive out through extra-cover, long chase for deep cover but gets there in time
whoops, long hop that Stokes whacks wide of deep cover
not as short and this is cut straight to the off side sweeper
short enough to cut again, this backward of deep cover for two
worked down the ground this time for a single to long-on
another long hop outside off, whacked to the extra-cover fence again
vaguely on a length and Stokes finds extra-cover this time
down the wicket and stroking this into the sightscreen, glorious shot, such timing
steps away and late cuts from the off stump to backward point
full on the leg stump and swept out to backward square who does well to save the second, great work
waited for in the crease and cut out to deep cover
full on middle and leg and Morgan swings it just wide of mid-on diving to his left, decent clunk and just in the gap
cut out wide of deep cover, just a single again
short ball pulled out wide of deep midwicket, poor delivery well put away
not as short just outside off, this is dabbed out towards point
straighter line and pulled again, in the air but well short of deep square, cries of catch for a time

backs away to leg and tries to swing a full delivery through the off side but edges behind! Healthy edge to the keeper and the change of bowling works. A brief flurry from Stokes but perhaps not enough for this chase. He had a fair old swing once more here but nicked off here trying to belt another ball away, thin outside edge with Stokes slightly off balance and it was an easy catch for Ronchi
length ball sliding across the off stump, left alone
tighter line and Buttler taps this into the covers for an easy single
full delivery calmly dropped down to long-on
back pushing off the back foot past cover
forward playing with the angle through square leg, comfortable run
slashing backward of square but still too close to the sweeper for a second run
forward just outside off into the covers
straighter line, this is tucked out to the leg side sweeper
full length just outside off, beautiful cover drive but well saved by extra-cover
wider and cut, mistimed and backward point comes in to save this
gets the cut away this time, slashing wide of third man for a second
not quite as wide, another cut attempted and misses here
length on a tight line now and Buttler blocks back to the bowler
wide outside off, too wide and called wide
square slash, lands just short of backward point
back pressing to extra-cover
a step down the track to get to the pitch of this and then whacking a slog sweep over wide long-on, nailed it into the stands
angled in, Morgan nudges this down to long-on
drifts into the pads and a touch short, Buttler pulls it and beats the chase of deep square
touch straight again, this is delicately played inside short long leg for two
floated up on off stump, Buttler unleashes a slog sweep this time and hammers this into the stands behind midwicket, great timing
full length around middle and off, this is tucked to the left of midwicket for an easy single
length ball a foot outside off, mistimes back foot press into the covers, got a little big on him
back of a length just outside off, this times finds backward point with a push
short and Buttler is onto it in a flash to hammer it wide of midwicket, what timing here
fuller and just blocked out to midwicket
full length sliding across the right-hander who leaves this alone
length ball sliding across Morgan who back-cuts wide of third man but they decide against the second run
little foot movement in pressing this length ball from just outside off to cover
wide on the bowling crease, Buttler takes a big stride down the wicket and drives down the ground, doesn't time it but gets it inside mid-on and still enough pace to take it to the rope
another drive ball but this is off a thick inside edge to mid-on
pushing a little away from his body, Buttler drives out to mid-off

flicks at a ball just outside off, healthy outside edge and dropped at slip by Taylor. Straightforward chance to his right, two hands at chest height, simply burst through his hands, should have been grabbed
leans forward to drive down the ground, in the air the whole way and just short of the rope and just short of mid-off running back too
short and wide and again Buttler finds the fielder, this with a cut, missed out
firm drive off the front foot to mid-off and they take on the fielder and get home easily
back of a length just outside off, this is guided down fine of third man but Boult dives to his right and makes a superb save with one hand
forward running this out only to backward point now
length ball just outside off, this is driven in the air but inside mid-off and over his head anyway
full length just outside off, dropped wide of cover for a single, better from Buttler
down the track and crashes a ball outside off wide of deep cover, great timing, fifty for Morgan in 28 balls
stays in his ground this time and slaps a length ball inside mid-off, powered away again
tight line now from Southee and Morgan just blocks this into the covers
down the track again and with the ball sliding across Morgan there is room for him to free his arms, timed well again, over the in-field and well wide of the off side sweeper, great shot
goes for the yorker, ends up being a low full toss, this is tapped inside mid-off for an easy single
shows the stumps and smashes this straight down the ground, gorgeous timing, straight as dye towards the sightscreen
stepping to leg again, Santner followed him and Morgan just blocked in back up the pitch
down the wicket, meets this as a low full toss, taps to mid-on for an easy single
dragged down a little but Buttler only rocks back and pushes through the covers
poor ball down the leg side, this is swept past short long leg
another sweet strike straight down the ground, stepping to leg to give himself some room and timing it to absolute perfection, brilliant from Morgan
another fantastic piece of timing, drives a length delivery on the up through the covers and the sweeper had to hustle to cut that off
poor line, on the pads and he flicks it fine of short fine leg
pushed across outside off, driven to the sweeper
full, angled into the pads, glances into the leg side...no bat involved
short of a length, touch of extra bounce, pushed to point from the back foot
that's another drilled drive, skims straight to mid-off...not much missing the middle of the bat at the moment
over the wicket, nudged down the ground to long-on
round the wicket, pushed out to deep cover
touch flatter, pushed to midwicket
another wonderful strike, he shimmies to the leg side to open up the off then lofts this inside-out over extra cover
loses his shape a little this time as he goes for a sweep, comes off a bottom edge to short fine leg
full and straight, pushed to the on side, Santner dives and reaches the ball but can't stop the single although does produce a nifty throw into the stumps
there's the breakthrough for New Zealand! And it's that man Boult. Wasn't a great delivery, short of a length and angled across Buttler who went for the cut and got a thin toe end low to Ronchi
short of a length outside off again, driven off the back foot to short cover
picks out cover with another drive
well bowled, beats the outside edge with one that seams away a touch although a half-hearted shot from Billings
comes round the wicket, tucks this delivery into the square-leg area
back over the wicket, fired in full wide of leg stump and he doesn't get away with it
full outside off, he goes for an expansive drive but Boult gets a hand on it in his follow through and mid-off tides up...good over from Boult
full outside off, worked to the leg side
comes nicely forward into a drive which finds Brendon McCullum at mid-off
on a length, dropped into the off side
that's a crunching drive, drills it straight back down the pitch, the latest batsman to trust the trueness of this pitch
now he slaps one through the covers, gets it well in front of square and the sweeper has to scurry around
round the wicket, full outside off, 81mph, driven to mid-off
low full toss at the stumps, clubbed with plenty of bottom hand to long-on
round the wicket, back of a length, Billings tries to pull but gets taken in the stomach
another short ball, angled into leg stump, he swivels on it and pulls to long leg
uses his feet, makes this into a full toss but doesn't time it very well and the ball bobbles down the ground
well bowled, cramped him for room with a shorter delivery which angled in from round the wicket, beats the top edge as Billings tries to steer down to third man
goes for the pull, not much timing into midwicket as the round-the-wicket line doesn't offer him any room...another good over from Boult
round the wicket, back of a length, blocked down by his feet and Morgan is quick to call him through
massive moment! Morgan finds deep point. He came down the pitch, aimed in the air over the off side again but got it too square and Elliott barely had to move on the boundary
round the wicket, short and pulled to deep square leg
beaten as he tries to angle a length delivery to third man
well bowled, full and angling in from round the wicket, defended
good stuff from McClenaghan, Rashid can't find space into the off side...excellent cover
and another! Some width outside off, Billings going for the cut but couldn't keep it down and finds backward point
defended to the off side
pulls a short delivery, comes from high on the pad and loops wide of mid-on
they'll keep in swinging, Plunkett now lofts a length delivery of mid-off and although it comes off near the bottom of bat it had plenty on it
oh dear! That was has slipped out...an attempted slower ball goes all wrong and barely lands on the cut strip
charge and a miss this time, the ball angling and beats leg stump
excellent delivery, gets the yorker in at Plunkett's boot from round the wicket
swats this through the off side with a strong mow
angled in from that round-the-wicket line, pushed into the off side and Rashid wanted a single but was sent back
edged, but short! He went for the pull, came off the bottom edge but it died in front of Ronchi
hammered through the off side, full outside off, he just stands there and drives powerfully wide of mid-off
dragged down short, he pulls through square leg but there's a man in the deep
swing and a miss to a full delivery outside off
dropped, again by Taylor, and his parry falls just out of reach of Ronchi...he actually did well to get a hand on it, was travelling quickly from Rashid's cut shot
goes full and straight, gets clubbed down the ground straight of mid-on
backs away to the leg side against a shorter delivery and then runs this wide of slip to third man
tries to pull a short ball, ends up finding mid-off
full and straight, slotted down the ground between long-off and long-on
full at the stumps, gives himself a touch of room and drives to the sweeper
floated up, Rashid gives himself room and it slices towards short third man
uses his feet and pings this very sweetly straight down the ground to beat the diving long-on
swing and a miss outside off, called wide
full at the stumps, heaved into the leg side
connects very cleanly with a sweep, reached out for the ball but managed to roll his wrists and skim it through square leg
nicely bowled, held back a fraction, just spun a little, Rashid adjusted from what looked like it would be another sweep and dabbed towards short third man
over the wicket, Plunkett is down the pitch and clubs towards long-on without making a particularly clean connection
length ball at the stumps, this is flicked out through midwicket for a couple
bumper, on line, Plunkett sways out of the way
down the track, aims a smash leg side but gets hit on the body and it loops to slip
full and wide, this is reached for and carved out to deep cover
yorker on off stump, dug out down the ground and they get just a single to long-on
low full toss carved only to backward point
low full toss, Rashid can only plunk it down well short of long-on

another low full toss, Plunkett swings at this and gets a thick outside edge that loops towards point, Guptill goes back to take the catch and drops it! He ran past it, had to reach back and couldn't cling on
in the slot to strike and heaves it over wide long-on, big blow
excellent delivery, full and wide of off stump, Plunkett does really well to drop this wide of third man and they sprint back for the second
very full again, this is on off stump and dug out past the bowler, long-on comes to his left to save really well and it's just two more
down the pitch, slices this out to deep cover just a single
oh brilliant, down the wicket, playing in-to-out strokes it wide of long-on! What timing on this
down the track, bowler drops his length, Plunkett taps it out through midwicket and they consider a second but the deep fielder does really well
back away to leg and dabs only as far as short third man
gives himself room outside leg and swings this over extra-cover, plenty on it and beats the fielder! One bounce over the rope
flat delivery beats the attempted cut stroke
fires this into the pads, Rashid looking to turn it to leg gets struck on the pad and the keeper is able to field
full outside off and just inside the guideline, that is Southee's very own delivery
similar ball, this driven to extra-cover, they run regardless and get home
full again, this is driven out wide of deep cover but Rashid slips so they can't even consider the second
similar area, Plunkett carves this to deep cover
what a shot, step across the stumps and flicks this from outside off through square leg, spotted the gap and found the rope
full ball outside off, swing and a miss from Rashid
down the track and slapped straight back to the bowler
touch short and Plunkett pulls it over midwicket! Big blow and England are up and running again, big strike into the stand, poor ball
length ball, slapped back onto the bowler again!

aims off side with all the fielders up but doesn't get all of it and finds mid-off jogging back! Slightly off balance trying to swing over the off side and didn't time this at all and Brendon McCullum went back a few yards to take an easy catch
steps to leg and slaps this over cover, great timing and a badly-needed boundary

slapped down the ground has Rashid done this here, no!! Long-on come around to take the catch but he's running over the rope so throws it back and then another catch! What a superb piece of fielding and surely that's the game. Tim Southee with the initial catch, realised he was going over the rope so flicked the ball back at the last second but Boult was there in time to reach up with a left-hand and make the second grab. What a bit of work, typically brilliant from New Zealand
full between the batsman and stumps, Finn swings and misses, Jordan runs a bye and Finn scrambles up the other end in time
full outside off, slapped to deep cover and they come back for two
plunked down the ground, to long-off and that will do it, just a single
full toss wide of off stump, Finn whacks it wide of midwicket
another leg side heave, this time deep midwicket comes to his left to field
length ball, swing and a miss
